<TITLE> Channel i's Mahbub Matin dies aged 39 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 10 (bdnews24.com)  Channel i joint news editor Mahbub Matin died of a heart attack at his home on Saturday, aged just 39. A statement, signed by News and Current Affairs editor of Channel i Saiful Amin, said that Mahbub died at dawn on Friday. Staff reporter at the private television channel, Niladri Shekhar Pintu, told bdnews24.com, "Matin died of cardiac arrest at his Sidheswari home." The journalist, whose home district was Comilla, attended his last day of office on Friday. A namaj-e-janaza was set for 8.30pm Saturday in front of the Channel i Siddheswari office. His body will then be held at BIRDEM hospital. It will be kept at the Dhaka Reporters Unity from 12am to 1pm on Sunday for colleagues and friends to pay their last repsects. He will be buried on Sunday at Azimpur graveyard following a second namaj-e-janaza after Zohr prayers at Dhaka University. Matin was born on July 22, 1970. He received an MA in Bangla from Dhaka University and worked for a time as a reporter for the Bangla-language daily Sangbad. He left behind wife Shahin Shabnam and their seven year old son Mounoprio Mahian bdnews24.
